From: Yan Zhao <yan.y.zhao@intel.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2020 03:12:34 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] vfio: avoid possible overflow in vfio_iommu_type1_pin_pages
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.6.11
Git-commit: 0ea971f8dcd6dee78a9a30ea70227cf305f11ff7

commit 0ea971f8dcd6dee78a9a30ea70227cf305f11ff7 upstream.

add parentheses to avoid possible vaddr overflow.

Fixes: a54eb55045ae ("vfio iommu type1: Add support for mediated devices")
Signed-off-by: Yan Zhao <yan.y.zhao@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Williamson <alex.williamson@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/vfio/vfio_iommu_type1.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/vfio/vfio_iommu_type1.c b/drivers/vfio/vfio_iommu_type1.c
index a177bf2c6683..ec9be79ba2d7 100644
--- a/drivers/vfio/vfio_iommu_type1.c
+++ b/drivers/vfio/vfio_iommu_type1.c
@@ -554,7 +554,7 @@ static int vfio_iommu_type1_pin_pages(void *iommu_data,
 			continue;
 		}
 
-		remote_vaddr = dma->vaddr + iova - dma->iova;
+		remote_vaddr = dma->vaddr + (iova - dma->iova);
 		ret = vfio_pin_page_external(dma, remote_vaddr, &phys_pfn[i],
 					     do_accounting);
 		if (ret)
